Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora to sharpish turn. Clay near fine pink-buff; cream slip. Rectangular stamp with pilos symbol in each corner.
Curator's comments: Name Iason. Trimmed. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0367.40.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1056)
